				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">psycopathicteen wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Is there anyway to get IRQs to fire immediately to fast ROM region?</div><br />The interrupt vectors are 16 bit words pointing to bank $00, so no. One common pattern is to have an indirect long jump at that address, so the vectors can be reconfigured via software and consequently you can also spend as little time as possible in slow addressing space.<br /><br />For &quot;one h-irq per line&quot; schemes like those discussed here you kinda spend too much time with setup either way... Timed &quot;speedcode&quot; seems like a better solution. I'm not sure if DRAM refresh and other factors are entirely deterministic across different consoles though (but then again the PPU revision is known, so it would suffice if the timing is known to be deterministic for all consoles with the same chipset).</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

